	narrator	Adam	male	Story narrator
	Vortigern	Daniel	male	1. Usurper king of Britain, cowardly and treacherous, who summoned Merlin to find a child born without mortal father to build his castle. He was ultimately burned alive in his tower by Aurelius.
	Merlin	Fable	*male	1. Young boy with mysterious parentage, claimed to be born without a mortal father. He is the son of the foul fiend according to some, but proves himself a powerful prophet and magician who foretells Arthur's birth. He serves as advisor to the kings and helps build Stonehenge. | 2. A powerful wizard who guides Arthur's rise to power, arranging for Arthur to be raised by Sir Ector and ensuring his true parentage remains hidden until the sword test. | 3. A mysterious figure who appears as both a child and an old man. He prophesies Arthur's death, reveals his true identity to him, and helps guide the king. | 5. The wise wizard who appears throughout the story, warning Sir Balin about his actions and their consequences. He is a prophetic figure who knows the future and guides characters with cryptic prophecies about doom and destruction. | 6. The wise wizard and advisor to King Arthur, who prophesies the misery that will come from Arthur's marriage to Guinevere. He plays a key role in organizing the Round Table and its founding ceremonies.
	Uther	Liam	male	1. King of Britain, brother of Aurelius and father of Arthur. He marries Igerna after the death of Gorlois, and is poisoned by Saxons while sick at Verulum. He becomes known as Uther Pendragon after Merlin's prophecy.
	Arthur	Onyx	*male	2. The rightful king of England, son of Uther and Arthur's father. A young man of fifteen years who is fair, tall, comely, strong, gentle in manner, and accomplished in knightly exercises. He draws the sword from the stone, proving his right to rule.
	Ector	Michael	*male	2. Arthur's foster father, a knight who raised Arthur as his own son. He discovers Arthur's true parentage and becomes loyal to him after the sword test.
	Brice	Echo	*male	2. The Archbishop of Canterbury who convenes the lords and barons to determine Arthur's succession through the sword test.
	King of the Hundred Knights	Alex	*male	2. A powerful king who joins Lot in his strategy during the Battle of Bedgraine.
	King Arthur	Eric	male	3. The main protagonist, king of Britain who drives the Saxons from his realm. He is a brave warrior who fights battles, leads armies, and has a prophetic dream about fiery griffins and serpents. He is known for his strength, honor, and leadership. | 4. The ruler of Britain, a valiant conqueror who has subdued Ireland, Iceland, Norway, Dacia, and Gaul. He is known for his strength, courage, and determination to avenge wrongs. He draws the sword Excalibur from a stone and is deeply involved in battles against giants, Romans, and other enemies. He shows both mercy and justice, as seen when he forgives Balin after his impulsive killing of the lady of the lake. | 5. The king of Britain who is the central figure in the court. He seeks justice for his enemies and becomes a prisoner of Sir Balin and Sir Balan after their successful attack on King Ryence. | 6. The king of Britain who desires to marry Guinevere and founds the Round Table. He is noble, bounteous, and seeks counsel from Merlin. | 7. The sovereign king of Britain, tall and strong, known for his knightly virtues. He is betrayed by Morgan le Fay into a false battle with Sir Accolon, who uses a counterfeit sword to wound him severely. He ultimately reveals his identity and defeats Sir Accolon, showing mercy despite the betrayal. | 8. Emperor of Rome, descended from Belinus and Brennius, son of Helen, claiming right to Roman Empire through ancestry. He is the central figure who refuses tribute from Rome and leads military campaigns against Lucius Tiberius. He is described as manly-seeming, strong enough to keep his kingdoms without paying tribute, and ultimately crowned Emperor in Rome. | 11. The king of Camelot, holding the Feast of Pentecost and ruling the Table Round. He grants knights' requests and is a central figure in the court's affairs. | 12. The legendary king of Britain, ruler of Camelot and leader of the Round Table. He holds high festivals at Caerleon and is a central figure in Arthurian legend, known for his wisdom, justice, and chivalry. | 13. The king of Camelot who presides over the Round Table. He receives news about the Sangreal quest and calls together his knights. | 14. The king of Camelot and leader of the Round Table. He is deeply concerned about his queen's honor and seeks justice for her. He shows great respect for Sir Lancelot, even when he is angry with him. | 15. The rightful king of Britain, leader of the Round Table knights. He is torn between his love for Lancelot and his duty to uphold honor, ultimately leading to a devastating civil war.
	King Ban	Puck	male	3. One of Arthur's companions who joins him in battle against Ryence. He later departs to deal with King Claudas.
	Griflet	Omega	*male	3. A young squire who is knighted by Arthur to avenge his master Nirles's death. He is defeated in combat but survives.
	King Ryence	George	male	4. The King of North Wales who sends a threatening message to King Arthur demanding his beard. He is described as proud and haughty, with eleven defeated kings whose beards he has used to trim a mantle. | 5. A king who is captured by Sir Balin and Sir Balan after they defeat his army. He seeks mercy from the knights but is ultimately delivered to King Arthur.
	Balin le Savage	Nicola	*male	4. A poor knight who has been imprisoned at King Arthur's court for slaying a cousin of the king. He is known for his gentle blood and valiant address, but was initially ashamed to try the sword. He successfully draws Excalibur from its scabbard, proving himself worthy.
	The Lady of the Lake	Siwis	*female	4. A mysterious woman who appears at the court and demands the head of Balin or the damsel who brought him the sword. She is revealed to be the murderer of Balin's mother and his enemy. | 10. A mysterious figure who rescued young Lancelot after his parents' death and raised him with his cousins Lionel and Bors in the lake.
	The Damsel	Jessica	*female	4. A mysterious woman who brings the sword Excalibur to King Arthur's court. She claims it can only be drawn by a faithful, pure, and true knight without guile or treachery. She is the one who warns Balin about keeping the sword. | 11. A young woman who seeks help for her lady, the Lady Lyones. She is initially skeptical of Beaumains but later shows respect.
	Sir Noran	Fable	*male	4. A knight in King Arthur's court who knows King Ryence and warns the king that he is proud, haughty, and likely to wage war with Arthur.
	The Squire	Liam	*male	4. Balin's companion who accompanies him after he departs from King Arthur's court. He expresses concern about Balin's actions and warns him of displeasing the king. | 9. A squire who leads a Spanish charger and is described as tall and strong. He attempts to take Sir Gawain's armor but is deterred by Gawain.
	Sir Balin	Daniel	male	5. A knight of Arthur's court, known as 'the knight of the two swords' after his adventure with the lady of the lake. He is a valiant warrior who fights in defense of honor and justice, but his actions lead to tragic consequences including the deaths of several knights. He is deeply remorseful for his mistakes and ultimately becomes a wanderer cursed by his 'Dolorous Stroke'.
	Sir Lancear	Fenrir	male	5. A knight of King Arthur's court who becomes envious of Sir Balin. He pursues Balin to avenge what he sees as an insult to the court, leading to their fatal duel. He is killed by Balin in combat and his lady-love Colombe kills herself upon seeing his death.
	Sir Balan	Michael	male	5. Sir Balin's brother who joins him in his quest to help King Arthur. He is also a valiant knight and ultimately becomes the one who kills Sir Balin in their final duel on the island, leading to both of their deaths.
	Sir Herleus	Kumo	*male	5. A knight who is slain by the invisible knight Garlon. He warns Sir Balin of Garlon's treachery and asks him to avenge his death.
	Sir Garlon	George	*male	5. An invisible knight who uses magic and witchcraft to slay knights. He is the main antagonist of this chapter, responsible for killing Sir Herleus and Sir Perin. He is ultimately slain by Sir Balin in a duel.
	King Pelles	Lewis	*male	5. The king who holds the holy Sangreal and is killed by Sir Balin in a fit of rage during the Listeniss feast. His death causes great destruction and is considered the 'Dolorous Stroke'.
	Sir Balin le Savage	Daniel	male	5. The same character as Sir Balin, but specifically identified in the final section of the story. He is a wandering knight who has been cursed by his actions and carries deep guilt.
	The Lady of the Castle	Xiaoyi	*female	5. A noblewoman who rules a castle where the damsel must give blood to cure her sick lady. She is also involved in the final confrontation with Sir Balin.
	The Host	Eric	*male	5. A rich man who hosts Sir Balin and his companions at a feast. He is the father of a son wounded by Garlon, who seeks revenge.
	Tor	Santa	*male	6. The son of Aries, later revealed to be the son of King Pellinore. He is knighted by Arthur and becomes a notable figure in the Round Table.
	King Pellinore	Echo	male	6. The father of Tor, who arrives at the court and is knighted. He is a great and valiant knight known for his prowess.
	Sir Gawain	George	male	6. King Arthur's nephew who is knighted and later becomes involved in the adventure of the white hart. He is angry at King Pellinore's honor and seeks to avenge his father. | 8. Knight of the Round Table, nephew to King Arthur. He is sent to confront Emperor Lucius and engages in combat with a Tuscan knight named Prianius. He is wounded but healed by the balm of Paradise. | 9. A knight of King Arthur's Round Table, known for his honor and chivalry. He is accused of treason and must defend himself in a royal court, leading him to refrain from participating in the tournament. He ultimately proves his worth by defeating Meliance of Lis and earning the admiration of the people. | 10. A knight of King Arthur's court who mistakes Sir Lancelot for Sir Key. | 11. A knight of the Round Table and brother to Sir Gareth. He recognizes Beaumains as his younger brother Gareth. | 12. A knight of King Arthur's court who helps Sir Tristram in various adventures. | 13. A knight of the Round Table who receives a message from Merlin about the Sangreal quest. He vows to seek it for twelve months and a day. | 14. A knight of the Round Table and brother to other notable knights. He is involved in a plot against Queen Guinevere, which leads to the death of Sir Patrice. He later seeks out Sir Lancelot and discovers his true identity. | 15. King Arthur's nephew and a knight of the Round Table. He becomes Lancelot's sworn enemy after believing Lancelot killed his brothers Sir Gareth and Sir Gaheris in battle.
	Gaheris	George	*male	6. Sir Gawain's brother who serves as his squire in the adventure of the white hart. He is present during Gawain's trial for slaying a lady.
	Allardin of the Isles	Fable	*male	6. A knight who fights Sir Gawain in a joust over the white hart. He is defeated and killed by Gawain.
	Abellius	Daniel	*male	6. A knight who fights Sir Tor over a hound. He is defeated and killed by Tor.
	Hantzlake of Wentland	Lewis	*male	6. A knight who fights King Pellinore for a lady. He is defeated and killed by Pellinore.
	The Lady	River	*female	6. A lady who is captured by a knight and later rescued by King Pellinore. She is revealed to be the daughter of King Pellinore.
	The Dwarf	Michael	*male	6. A mysterious figure who blocks Sir Tor's path and later serves as his companion. | 7. A servant of Morgan le Fay who delivers Excalibur to Sir Accolon. He is part of the enchantment that leads to the battle between Arthur and Accolon.
	Sir Accolon of Gaul	Fenrir	male	7. A knight from Gaul who is tricked by Morgan le Fay into fighting King Arthur. He becomes a traitor, believing he's serving his sister Morgan le Fay in her plot to kill Arthur. He reveals himself as a loyal knight of Arthur's court after the battle.
	Sir Damas	Onyx	male	7. A treacherous knight who is the antagonist of this chapter. He imprisons knights and forces them to fight his brother Outzlake, or face death. He is the false knight who tricks Arthur into a battle with Accolon.
	Damsel of Morgan le Fay	Kore	*female	7. A false damsel who claims to be a servant of Morgan le Fay but is actually one of her agents. She deceives Arthur with false promises and later reveals herself to be a witch who is burned by the cursed mantle.
	Lucius Tiberius	Eric	male	8. Emperor of Rome who demands tribute and homage from King Arthur. He is the primary antagonist, leading a massive army against Britain, ultimately defeated and killed by King Arthur in battle at Soissons. He is described as angry when ambassadors return with refusal to submit.
	Sir Cador of Cornwall	Psi	male	8. Knight of the Round Table who speaks first at the council, advocating for war against Rome. He is chosen to convey King Arthur's message to the Roman ambassadors and later sent to escort them out of Britain.
	King Anguish of Scotland	Nicola	male	8. Scottish king who swears to avenge Rome's past oppression and promises twenty thousand men-at-arms to King Arthur.
	Sir Bors	Puck	male	8. Knight of the Round Table who accompanies Sir Gawain in confronting Emperor Lucius. He fights valiantly against Romans and is captured but later freed by Sir Gawain. | 12. A knight who initially refuses to fight Sir Tristram but later acknowledges his prowess. | 13. A knight of the Round Table who sets out on the quest for the Sangreal. He is Sir Lionel's brother. | 14. A noble knight of the Round Table and close companion to Sir Lancelot. He serves as a mediator between Arthur and Guinevere, and later becomes the queen's champion in her trial by combat. He is deeply loyal to Lancelot and feels responsible for the injury he caused.
	Sir Ganius	Nicola	*male	8. A knight and cousin of Emperor Lucius who laughs at the Britons' boasting, leading to his death by Sir Gawain's sword.
	Prianius	Liam	*male	8. Tuscan knight who fights Sir Gawain and is wounded. He becomes a Christian after being healed by the balm of Paradise.
	Thiebault of Tintagel	Psi	male	9. The lord of the castle who organized the tournament against Meliance of Lis. He is initially suspicious of Gawain but later shows him honor and hospitality.
	Garin	Echo	*male	9. A nobleman who takes Sir Gawain in as a guest at his house. He is the father of Herman and stands up to Thiebault when he accuses Gawain.
	Maid with the Narrow Sleeves	Nova	*female	9. The younger daughter of Thiebault, known for her tight sleeves. She is the one who initiates the tournament by challenging Meliance of Lis's superiority and later asks Sir Gawain to participate in the tourney.
	Elder daughter of Thiebault	Lily	*female	9. The older daughter of Thiebault who is jealous and angry with her younger sister. She beats the Maid with the Narrow Sleeves after a quarrel over Sir Gawain's prowess.
	Sir Lancelot	Lewis	male	10. Son of King Ban of Brittany, knight of the Round Table known as Lancelot du Lake. Famous for his prowess in jousts and battles, he is the most celebrated knight at the Pentecost feast. He has a deep affection for Queen Guinevere and is renowned for his strength, honor, and adventures. | 11. A knight of the Round Table who knights Beaumains and is a key figure in Arthur's court. | 12. A renowned knight of the Round Table, known as one of the greatest knights in Arthurian legend. He is described as peerless in courtesy and knighthood, and his name carries great respect among knights. | 13. A knight of the Round Table who is called by a mysterious lady to join the quest for the Sangreal. He is also the father of Sir Galahad. | 14. The noblest knight in the world, known for his prowess in battle and quests. He is deeply loved by Queen Guinevere but maintains a complex relationship with her due to his chivalric duties and honor. He is wounded during the tournament at Camelot, leading to a period of recovery in the hermitage. | 15. The central knight of the Round Table, renowned for his prowess in battle and his affair with Queen Guinevere. He is portrayed as a noble but flawed hero who becomes embroiled in a war with King Arthur due to his relationship with the queen.
	Sir Turquine	Lewis	male	10. A powerful and cruel knight who imprisons knights of the Round Table. He is obsessed with killing Sir Lancelot, whom he believes killed his brother Sir Carados.
	Queen Morgan le Fay	Dora	female	10. King Arthur's half-sister and a powerful sorceress. She captures Sir Lancelot in an enchanted sleep, tries to force him to serve her, and is one of the four queens who imprison him.
	King Bagdemagus	Alex	male	10. A noble king who holds a tournament against the King of Northgales. He is helped by Sir Lancelot in defeating his enemies. | 13. A king who attempts to bear the shield of the monastery but is wounded by a White Knight.
	Sir Phelot	Alex	male	10. A knight of the King of Northgales who tries to kill Sir Lancelot after his wife tricks him into believing Lancelot is the enemy.
	Sir Pedivere	Onyx	male	10. A knight who kills his own wife and then tries to kill Sir Lancelot. He is defeated by Lancelot but later repents and becomes a hermit.
	Beaumains	Alex	*male	11. A kitchen servant who becomes Sir Gareth of Orkney, a noble knight. He is strong and brave, having overcome many knights including Sir Key, Sir Lancelot, the Black Knight, Green Knight, Red Knight, and others.
	Sir Key	Omega	male	11. A knight who mistreats Beaumains in the kitchen but is later defeated by him. | 12. A knight who challenges Sir Tristram to a joust and is defeated by him. | 13. The seneschal of King Arthur's court who reminds the king about ancient customs.
	Lady Lyones	Sara	*female	11. The lady besieged by the Red Knight, who is later rescued by Sir Gareth. She falls in love with him and becomes his wife.
	Knight of the Redlands	Santa	*male	11. The tyrant who besieges Lady Lyones. He is later revealed to be Sir Ironside, a knight seeking revenge for his lady's brother.
	Sir Gareth of Orkney	Omega	*male	11. The true identity of Beaumains, revealed to be the youngest brother of Sir Gawain and son of King Lot.
	Sir Perseant	Santa	*male	11. A knight who is defeated by Sir Gareth and later becomes his ally.
