	Sir Tristram	Kumo	male	12. A noble knight of Lyonesse, son of King Meliodas and Queen Elizabeth. Known for his strength, skill in battle, and tragic love for La Belle Isault. He fought Sir Marhaus of Ireland, overcame Sir Palomedes at a tournament, and was involved in many adventures including his time in Ireland where he was betrayed by the queen. He is a key figure in Arthurian legend, known for his valor and honor.
	King Mark	Nicola	male	12. The king of Cornwall and uncle to Sir Tristram. He is initially welcoming but later becomes jealous of Tristram's fame and favors, eventually plotting against him.
	La Belle Isault	Emma	*female	12. The daughter of King Anguish of Ireland, later married to King Mark. She is described as fair and noble, and becomes the object of Sir Tristram's love and devotion.
	King Meliodas	Santa	male	12. The king of Lyonesse and father of Sir Tristram. He is married to Queen Elizabeth, who dies in childbirth.
